Production deploys are FROZEN until the P2 content cutover (MS2-FR-29c).

Why: worker sources now serve the v2 schema (translations table, composite
hashes). Production's CONTENT_DB still points at the legacy v1 database, which
has no translations table — deploying this code to prod before the cutover
would 500 every data request.

Lifted by the cutover step itself: publish v2 content to german-content-prod,
flip the CUTOVER(P2) bindings in both wrangler.toml files, delete this file,
then scripts/deploy.sh prod in the same change.
